{"type": "article", "id": 23032, "title": "墨尔本这家日本餐厅，寿司区与烧烤区有两种“情绪”", "description": "毕竟吃寿司和吃烧烤的氛围还是有差别的嘛。\r\n", "date": "2016-03-01T08:00:00Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 4814, "name": "餐厅设计"}, {"id": 435, "name": "室内设计"}, {"id": 10665, "name": "品牌设计"}], "category": 17, "author": 1329, "comment_count": 2, "praise_count": 194, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160702165012bVfwYces7WUtjElS.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p>在百货商场的餐饮区域，餐厅设计限于商场的条条框框，总是很难做出新意。但最近在墨尔本 Emporium 商场，一家名为「Tetsujin」的日本餐厅倒是在空间设计上花了些心思。</p>\n<p>操刀这一空间设计的是墨尔本 Architects EAT 事务所，而负责餐厅品牌设计的亦是墨尔本当地的 Principle Design 工作室。</p>\n<p>Tetsujin 主打两种风格的料理，一是日式烧肉，一是回转寿司，这种混搭的感觉也体现在设计中。整个空间以轻松、明亮的氛围为主调，横竖交叉的纯白色条状物构筑出一个醒目的天花板结构，原木色地板与白色瓷砖搭配的空间主背景则透着清爽宜人的味道。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702165005gPrJCviaILtX8YRD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>\n<p>但在回转寿司区与烧烤酒吧区，空间设计又呈现出细微的情绪差别，前者用白色的环形吊灯灯管围出一圈明亮的用餐区域，而烧烤酒吧区域的着色就要浓郁一些。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-images-wide\">\n<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702165006VHyLuIh2ex1KltD8.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66629213\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">寿司区</div></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702165006q3QaceVl5pPrOfhU.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">寿司区</div></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607021650074zPwV69MSNQeE8fR.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">烧烤区</div></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702165007KNFd0kcJGZ74xtYq.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.69494949\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure>\n</div>\n<p>两个工作室在整体空间的视觉语言设计上达成了一致，皆是以日本火车文化以及在日本极其流行的自动贩卖机为灵感，尤其是 Principle Design 创造的一系列以机器人、相机等图案为主的平面视觉图贯穿在餐厅中，给予食客视觉上的直接冲击力。而 Architects EAT 则将这些元素进行解构，用相近的色彩、烧烤炉的金属质感等来表现，期望能够调动起食客在不同区域的不同情绪。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\">\n<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702165008h7C2uk6jqQJwSL1B.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66741573\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">工作服</div>\n<p></p></figcaption></figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702165008Q5LbkriXJAp9xBlI.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure>\n</div>\n<p>从 Architects EAT 事务所的名字便不难看出，这是一间擅于餐厅设计的事务所。最后不妨来看看他们的其他餐厅作品。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702165009CTQpFzcWvOxesP5D.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">8bit City 餐厅</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702165009gjZOzXUtCJc6H53v.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">Fafah Chadstone 餐厅</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702165010J7X3UuhSptKvGBwH.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">Pabu Bar 餐厅</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201607021650102KMo7f3Fmet6Y48c.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.77272727\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">Sushi hon 餐厅</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-active\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702165011eGv2h6rVfDdIYF1N.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.74343434\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\"><div style=\"text-align: center;\">Xeom 餐厅</div></figcaption></figure></div>\n<p>图片来自<a href=\"http://eatas.com.au/projects/detail/tetsujin-emporium\"> Architects EAT </a></p>\n\n"}